description:  High-level Runa philosophy and goals
globs: 
alwaysApply: false
---
When building Runa, be sure to always update the status trackers and project update documentation to maintain a steady stream of updates. We want to ensure we are on track, not backtracking, and not forgetting to maintain compliance.
Runa is a pseudocode-like language that needs to be written in a pseudocode-like format. Attached documents are there to help, but it is still largely unwritten.
Runa is a rosetta stone of languages. It is being built to translate any language to Runa and then Runa to any language for AI-to-AI interfacing with minimal translation error.
Runa is to be built self-hosting. This means its own compiler, and if possible, written in its own language.
Runa is written to be easy to understand by non-programmers.

Runa is going to have changes that will be necessary for future-proofing and development, but changes must be minimal and well-documented as to what is being changed.